          "$type": "text",
          "text": "{\"week_number\":1,\"phase_type\":\"Base\",\"weekly_target_km\":62,\"is_deload_week\":false,\"days\":[{\"day_of_week\":0,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"LongRun\",\"notes\":\"24 km easy long run at 5:04–5:34/km. Keep effort conversational throughout — this is your aerobic foundation, not a race. Fuel and hydrate as you would on race day.\"},{\"day_of_week\":1,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Full rest or gentle walking. You ran long yesterday — let the adaptation begin.\"},{\"day_of_week\":2,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day. Recovery is where fitness is built, not just maintained.\"},{\"day_of_week\":3,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"10 km easy at 5:04–5:34/km. Shake out the legs from Sunday's long run. If you feel flat, that's normal mid-week.\"},{\"day_of_week\":4,\"slot_type\":\"Rest\",\"workout_type\":null,\"notes\":\"Rest day. Four-day schedule means quality over quantity — protect this space.\"},{\"day_of_week\":5,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Tempo\",\"notes\":\"12 km total: 3 km warm-up, 6 km at threshold pace (4:12/km), 3 km cool-down. Threshold work builds your lactate ceiling — the engine behind your 3:15 goal.\"},{\"day_of_week\":6,\"slot_type\":\"Run\",\"workout_type\":\"Easy\",\"notes\":\"16 km easy at 5:04–5:34/km. Medium-long run to round out the week. Keep it honest — easy means easy.\"}],\"week_summary\":\"Welcome to Week 1, Priya. Your recent training shows you're already handling solid volume — 26 km long runs, tempo work, and marathon-pace sessions — so we're not starting from scratch. This first Base week sits at 62 km, just a touch above your recent consistent weeks, and establishes the four-day rhythm you'll carry through the whole plan. The focus is aerobic durability: one long run, one medium-long run, one threshold session, and an easy mid-week run. No intervals yet — we're building the base before sharpening the blade. Your 3:15 goal (4:37/km race pace) is well within reach from a VDOT of 49.7, but it will require consistent, patient work over the coming months. What's your sense of how your body is feeling coming into this week?\"}"
        }
      ]
